comments.comment_body:
@fischkopp. 
My son, his German girlfriend of 20 years, and my 8 year old grandson live in Dresden.  I visit often and am continually impressed with what a difference there is between childcare in Germany and childcare in the US.  Kindergeld is one asset but there are so many others that support a healthy environment for raising kids:  an emphasis on outdoor activities and being outside everyday.  Creative, multiple playgrounds.  Wonderful swimming pools for children and adults.  Subsidized quality preschools.  Healthy eating habits and many outdoor markets with daily fresh fruits and vegetables , generous childbirth benefits and vacation time that allow families to take the kids on frequent trips to interesting places, and the most priceless of all - National Health Care.

It is very hard to have a grandson a half a world away.  But I would much prefer that he be  raised in Germany and not here.
